They said little else as they followed . 
He went on before them as an ugly Fate might have done , and they kept him in view , and would have been glad enough to lose sight of him . 
But on he went before them , always at the same distance , and the same rate . 
Aslant against the hard implacable weather and the rough wind , he was no more to be driven back than hurried forward , but held on like an advancing Destiny . 
There came , when they were about midway on their journey , a heavy rush of hail , which in a few minutes pelted the streets clear , and whitened them . 
It made no difference to him . 
A man's life being to be taken and the price of it got , the hailstones to arrest the purpose must lie larger and deeper than those . 
The blast went by , and the moon contended with the fast flying clouds , and the wild disorder reigning up there made the pitiful little tumults in the streets of no account . 
'If he has had time to think of it , said Eugene , he has not had time to think better of it or differently of it , if that's better . 
