Boots and Brewer immediately perceive that it is immensely worth mentioning , and become politely clamorous . 
Veneering is also visited by a perception to the same effect . 
But it is understood that his attention is now rather used up , and difficult to hold , that being the tone of the House of Commons . 
'Pray don't be at the trouble of composing yourselves to listen , says Mortimer Lightwood , 'because I shall have finished long before you have fallen into comfortable attitudes . 
