He is a very good boy though , and has raised himself by his industry . 
I don't complain of him . 
As she said it , with her eyes upon the fire glow , there was an instantaneous escape of distress into her face . 
Bella seized the moment to touch her hand . 
'Lizzie , I wish you would tell me whether you have any friend of your own sex and age . 
'I have lived that lonely kind of life , that I have never had one , was the answer . 
'Nor I neither , said Bella . 
I wish you could make a friend of me , Lizzie . 
Do you think you could ? I have no more of what they call character , my dear , than a canary bird , but I know I am trustworthy . 
To Lizzie it was so new , so pretty , at once so womanly and so childish , that it won her completely . 
'Tell me , my dear , said Bella , 'what is the matter , and why you live like this . 
Lizzie presently began , by way of prelude , 'You must have many lovers when Bella checked her with a little scream of astonishment . 
'My dear , I haven't one ! 'Not one ? 'Well ! Perhaps one , said Bella . 
'I am sure I don't know . 
I HAD one , but what he may think about it at the present time I can't say . 
However , never mind me . 
I want to hear about you . 
'There is a certain man , said Lizzie , 'a passionate and angry man , who says he loves me , and who I must believe does love me . 
He is the friend of my brother . 
I shrank from him within myself when my brother first brought him to me but the last time I saw him he terrified me more than I can say . 
'Did you come here to escape from him , Lizzie ? 'I came here immediately after he so alarmed me . 
'Are you afraid of him here ? 'I am not timid generally , but I am always afraid of him . 
I am afraid to see a newspaper , or to hear a word spoken of what is done in London , lest he should have done some violence . 
'Then you are not afraid of him for yourself , dear ? said Bella , after pondering on the words . 
'I should be even that , if I met him about here . 
I look round for him always , as I pass to and fro at night . 
