'There is nothing left out . 
This is my reason for living secret here , with the aid of a good old man who is my true friend . 
For a short part of my life at home with father , I knew of things don't ask me what that I set my face against , and tried to better . 
I don't think I could have done more , then , without letting my hold on father go but they sometimes lie heavy on my mind . 
By doing all for the best , I hope I may wear them out . 
'And wear out too , said Bella soothingly , 'this weakness , Lizzie , in favour of one who is not worthy of it . 
I don't want to wear that out , was the flushed reply , 'nor do I want to believe , nor do I believe , that he is not worthy of it . 
