My dear friend Mr Eugene Wrayburn is dying . 
The dressmaker clasped her hands , and uttered a little piteous cry . 
'Is dying , repeated Lightwood , with emotion , 'at some distance from here . 
He is sinking under injuries received at the hands of a villain who attacked him in the dark . 
I come straight from his bedside . 
He is almost always insensible . 
